    "answer_id" : 2076073,
    "question_id" : 860187,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://www.digizol.com/2008/09/eclipse-access-restriction-on-library.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://www.digizol.com/2008/09/eclipse-access-restriction-on-library.html</a> worked best for me. </p>\n\n<p><strong>On Windows:</strong> Windows -> Preferences -> Java -> Compiler -> Errors/Warnings\n-> Deprecated and restricted API -> Forbidden reference (access rules): -> change to warning</p>\n\n<p><strong>On Mac OS X/Linux:</strong> Eclipse -> Preferences -> Java -> Compiler -> Errors/Warnings\n-> Deprecated and restricted API -> Forbidden reference (access rules): -> change to warning</p>\n"
