    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>for me this how I solve it:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>go to the <strong>build path</strong> of the current project</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>under Libraries</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>select the \"<strong>JRE System Library</strong> [jdk1.8xxx]\"</li>\n<li>click <strong>edit</strong></li>\n<li>and select either \"Workspace default JRE(jdk1.8xx)\" <strong>OR</strong> Alternate JRE</li>\n<li>Click finish</li>\n<li>Click OK</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/rzdkY.jpg\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/rzdkY.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p>Note: make sure that in Eclipse / Preferences (NOT the project) / Java / Installed JRE  ,that the jdk points to the JDK folder not the JRE <strong>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_74</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/MJHXA.jpg\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/MJHXA.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7826541,
      "reputation" : 29,
      "user_id" : 5917904,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fe03f041c0277a9b0567a3549193e102?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Abhishek Soni",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5917904/abhishek-soni"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1502865631,
    "creation_date" : 1502865631,
    "answer_id" : 45706645,
    "question_id" : 860187,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Adding a right JRE System through build path is the solution but your eclipse still may have the error.\nTo solve that go to Java Build path --> Order and Export and move your JRE system library on the top. This has solved my problem.</p>\n"
